I need to take a completely different approach. The interpreter is too slow at ~8M insns/sec. DOOM needs hundreds of millions of instructions. Let me use Node.js `new Function` to JIT compile MIPS blocks into JavaScript for 100x speed improvement.

{
  "analysis": "The interpreter runs at ~8M insns/sec but DOOM needs ~500M+ insns. Even at 500s that's not enough. I need a block-based JIT compiler. Let me write a JIT that translates basic blocks of MIPS into JavaScript functions that V8 can optimize. This should give 100-1000x speedup.",
  "plan": "Rewrite vm.js with a JIT compiler that translates MIPS basic blocks to JavaScript. Each block becomes a Function that V8's JIT can optimize aggressively.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "head -1 vm.js > /dev/null && wc -l vm.js\n",
      "duration": 0.1
